value.0: Though cooled long before your grandfather's grandfather was born, the idea of stepping into this foreboding lava tube starts you sweating from the imagined heat of the molten rock which once poured through it. You can dimly see such a reddish light from the end of the tube many meters away, and occasionally a waft of super-heated air drifts down the tube along with the thick smell of sulfur. Clearly the volcano that made this tube isn't entirely dormant...

A hefty supply of granite...
